<br>
 You where Kind enough to let me accompany you guys to fear today,and i Hope it gave a good impression of my abilities (my first time in a plane). I really enjoyed it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
 Ill include an application form sent to me from another guild it describes me pretty well (I hope hehe) and is kind of a poetic justice considering how that guild treated me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) hehe.<br>
<br>
1. Which CS members have you grouped with consistantly that know you well enough to accurately vouch for your playing skills? <br>
<br>
Ive Grouped with Giljabet and Elandire (as well as several others, please take no offence if i cant remember the names <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) several times in MWH and Auram is most likely willling to speak on my behalf too.<br>
<br>
<br>
2. What sort of groups or raids have you participated in? What are your experiences involving grouping with our members? Be as specific as possible. <br>
<br>
First and only raids i have participated in whas with CS this very day in fear<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br>
<br>
3.What is the most challening thing you've done in EQ? How would you rate your performance at that event? Be as specific as possible.<br>
<br>
It whas completing the Phenocryst`s focus Quest, not hard by itself (hardest part involves killing 1 level 50 cleric frost giant and 2 level 45 warrior classed frost giants) but getting enough ppls who where willing to help me whas a major pain. It took 2 weeks to get the ppls but i did it without incidents (crossing Kael almost ended badly though). Once in the wakening lands it whas a piece of cake. In short the hard part whas getting my 2 groups and getting them to the Wakening lands safely.<br>
<br>
4. How many hours do you currently play your MAIN character per week? During that time do you focus on leveling or helping others? <br>
<br>
My Main char is Meribeth. Been playing for only 5 months so i concentrated all my efforts on her , almost (i have a 13 uber twinked bard and 12 chanter). As for leveling or helping it depends, i do one or the other  depending on my motivations. As for helping others i usually do so when i have the time and inclinaison and rarely refuse to help a friend.I play maybe 30 hours per week, maybe more when i get someting that i really whant to do.<br>
<br>
5. Why do you play EverQuest?<br>
<br>
Why do ppls like having Fun? the game has infinite replay value because its a social game actual ppls are in it not just dumb NPCs , interaction, challenges ect (ive been in only one raid in fear and i can say its one heck of a rush seeing 30ppls beating the living crap outta ubermobs, so many working together its incredible)<br>
<br>
6. If you were given the chance to teach another player how to play your MAIN character, what would you tell them? How would you explain your mastery of the class to the other player so that he could play your character just as well as you can? What situational tips and tricks, and what specific playing methods are essential to your success?<br>
<br>
Well, when to start nuking is essential (if u piss off a mob too early your dead meat), how to group with others (telling a lost newbie hes a moron and such doesnt help with socials), been a wiz is pretty straightforward, wait till the tanks have beaten the mob to about half hp and start nuking, snares and root in cases of overburn ect... Also how to avoid crappy spells (NOBODY needs alkabor spells in my humbble opinion hehe, and elves have little use for an infravision spell but others could have use of it, in short analyse the spells and make your own mind).<br>
<br>
Develop an &quot;all purpose&quot; spell repertoire. In my case its a Stun, Primary DD, Secondary DD (preferably not of the same type like ice/fire), a Root, a Snare, a Shield, and a Gate of some sort to escape. This is how i do it but its not nessarly the best way feel free to develop your own.<br>
<br>
Getting Jboots is a debate thats not really a debate since they let you outrun most mobs. Find friends and get those as soon as possible.<br>
<br>
Informarion sites such as Castersrealm and Evelore where essential for my success id advise their Very frequent consultations. And above all COMMON SENCE please CONS that mob before starting to burn it, especially when soloing *recalls some bad souvenirs* hehe.<br>
<br>
<br>
 I hope i can see you soon as guild members.<br>
<br>
Thank you for your time.<br>
<br>
 Meribeth Silverlight<br>
